<textarea name="message" rows="12" cols="50" wrap="virtual" onkeyup="storeCaret(this);" onclick="storeCaret(this);">[QUOTE]Originally posted by Nong:
[QB]Guys, I found that reference to charisma I was talking about in the former thread. I think it speaks for itself. This is a transcript from the Dallas Fan Faire, and the speaker is Lawrence Poe. 

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
Q: Necromancers have really low charisma but get Fears and Charms which need it?  Doesn't this seem strange?

Poe: Charisma has nothing to do with resist rates on Fear spells, and has only a [b]minor[/b] help on the Charms.  It's got a lot more to do with levels for both of those, so the Necromancers don't really have too many problems with that
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

You can interpret that as you like, but the way I read it, charisma is a luxury, not a necessity.[/QB][/QUOTE]
